The paper deals with the information rates of OFDM in optical channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of power allocation strategies and codebook ensembles also suggests a possible connection to optimization (cs.OH). The study of optical intensity channels and power constraints is also relevant to the subfield of optical networking (cs.NI) and photonics (cs.PHOTONICS).
